snippet.title: Kai Trump - Thank You God For Grandpa (AI Music Video)
snippet.description:
Thank You, God, for Grandpa

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:

[Verse 1]
I wake up to the sunshine,
Flags waving in the breeze,
Secret Service near the garden,
But it still feels home to me.
Grandpa’s at the table,
Smiling like he always does,
Reading letters from the people,
Still believing just because.

[Chorus]
Thank You, God, for Grandpa,
You gave him strength to lead.
You held his hand through every storm,
Planted faith like a seed.
He taught me to stand tall,
To never run or hide.
Thank You, God, for Grandpa—
I’ve never been more proud inside.

[Verse 2]
He talks about our country
Like it’s part of who we are,
Tells me stories of the old days
When dreams could take you far.
He says freedom isn’t easy,
But it’s worth the fight and fire.
And every time he hugs me,
He lifts my spirit higher.

[Chorus]
Thank You, God, for Grandpa,
For showing me what’s true.
He prays before he speaks,
He fights for red, white, and blue.
He’s not just the president—
He’s the grandpa I adore.
Thank You, God, for Grandpa—
And the purpose You restored.

[Bridge]
I see the world watch him,
But I see him with my heart.
He’s just the one who held my hand
When the thunder made me start.
And now he holds a nation,
Like he once held me that night—
God, keep him strong and steady,
Keep him walking in Your light.

[Final Chorus]
Thank You, God, for Grandpa,
You made him brave and kind.
He carries so much on his back,
But never leaves love behind.
From the front steps of the White House
To the stories that he tells—
Thank You, God, for Grandpa—
And the way his courage swells.

[Outro]
Yeah, thank You, God, for Grandpa...
He’s the hero that I know.
And when I grow up, I’ll remember
The seeds of love he chose to sow.
